<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2069> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2069" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Possibly author of the Lex Atinia (Gell. 17.7.1) de usucapione." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2068> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2068" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Election Liv. 33.42.7 Provinces and armies 33.43.5-8." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2035> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2035" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Carried a bill authorizing five colonies (Liv. 32.29.3-4; see 197, Special Commissions), and joined Marcius Ralla in vetoing Marcellus' attempt to prevent peace with Philip (33.25.6-7). See above on Afranius." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/2034> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #2034" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Rather than assume that two persons named C. Atinius held the Tribunate of the Plebs in 197 and 196 respectively, it is better, with Niccolini (FTP 106f.), to consider that the Lex Atinia to found five maritime colonies was passed at the end of the consular year 197 (Liv. 32.29.3-4; see 197, Special Commissions), after the Tribunes for 196 had taken office." .
